Rowe, Morris and Wright from the battling era after the war; Richardson and Knights from recent times. But the great days from the late 1960s to the early 1980s provide the bulk of the side: Sheedy, Green, Keane, Bourke, Barrot, Clay, Hart, Dean and Bartlett who made up the core of Tom Hafey's teams, and later success stories Weightman and Raines. Ian Stewart, named on the bench, managed selection in a team of the century at two clubs\u2014he was named in the centre of St Kilda's team as well. Richmond has four players denoted below with an [[asterisk]] who are also members of [[AFL Team of the Century]]. This is the second-most of any club.\n\n{{Aussie rules team | title = Richmond Team of the Century\n| backpocket1 = [[Kevin Sheedy (Australian footballer)|Kevin Sheedy]]\n''1967\u201379, 180cm 81k,<br /> 251 games 91 goals''\n| fullback = [[Vic Thorp]]\n''1910\u201325, 178cm 83k,<br /> 263 games 7 goals''\n| backpocket2 = [[Michael Green (Australian rules footballer)|Michael Green]]\n''1966\u201375, 193cm 94k,<br /> 146 games 83 goals''\n| halfbackflank1 = [[Basil McCormack]]\n''1925\u201336, 180cm 80k,<br /> 199 games 1 goal''\n| centrehalfback = [[Gordon Strang]]\n''1931\u201338, 185cm 83k,<br /> 116 games 108 goals''\n| halfbackflank2 = [[Mervyn Keane]]\n''1972\u201384, 185cm 82k,<br /> 238 games 36 goals''\n| wing1 = [[Francis Bourke]] *\n''1967\u201381, 185cm 83k,<br /> 300 games 71 goals''\n| centre = [[Bill Barrot]]\n''1961\u201370, 180 cm 76k,<br /> 120 games 91 goals''\n| wing2 = [[Dick Clay]]\n''1966\u201376, 185cm 85k,<br /> 213 games 80 goals''\n| halfforwardflank1 = [[Matthew Richardson (footballer)|Matthew Richardson]]\n''1993\u20132009 , 197cm 103k,<br /> 282 games 800 goals''\n| centrehalfforward = [[Royce Hart]] *\n''1967\u201377, 187cm 86k,<br /> 187 games 369 goals''\n| halfforwardflank2 = [[Roger Dean (Australian rules footballer)|Roger Dean]]\n''1957\u201373, 175cm 73k,<br /> 245 games 204 goals''\n| forwardpocket1 = [[Dale Weightman]]\n''1978\u201393, 170cm 69k,<br /> 274 games 344 goals''\n| fullforward = [[Jack Titus]]\n''1926\u201343, 175cm 66k,<br /> 294 games 970 goals''\n| forwardpocket2 = [[Bill Morris (Australian rules footballer)|Bill Morris]]\n''1942\u201351, 188cm 86k,<br /> 140 games 98 goals''\n| ruck = [[Roy Wright (footballer)|Roy Wright]]\n''1946\u201359, 188cm, 102k,<br /> 195 games 127 goals''\n| ruckrover = [[Jack Dyer]] * (capt)\n''1931\u201349, 185cm 89k,<br /> 312 games 443 goals''\n| rover = [[Kevin Bartlett (Aussie Rules footballer)|Kevin Bartlett]]\n''1965\u201383, 175cm 71k,<br /> 403 games 778 goals''\n| interchange1 = [[Des Rowe]]\n''1946\u201357, 182cm 83k,<br /> 175 games 24 goals''\n| interchange2 = [[Geoff Raines]]\n''1976\u201382, 180cm 78k,<br /> 134 games 53 goals''\n| interchange3 = [[Ian Stewart (Australian rules footballer)|Ian Stewart]] *\n''1971\u201375, 180cm 78k,<br /> 78 games 55 goals''\n| interchange4 = [[Matthew Knights]]\n''1988\u20132002, 179cm 74k,<br /> 279 games 141 goals''\n| interchange5 = \n| interchange6 =\n| coach = [[Tom Hafey]]\n''Coached 248 Won 173 Lost 73 Drawn 2''}}\n\n[http://www.richmondfc.com.au/TheClub/History/TeamoftheCentury/tabid/7669/Default.aspx]\n\n===Australian Football Hall of Fame members===\nAs legends of the game:\n*[[Jack Dyer]] (inaugural \"Legend\")\n*[[Kevin Bartlett (Aussie Rules footballer)|Kevin Bartlett]]\n*[[Ian Stewart (Australian rules footballer)|Ian Stewart]]\n*[[Royce Hart]]\n*[[Kevin Sheedy (Australian footballer)|Kevin Sheedy]]\nAs players of the game:\n*[[Percy Bentley]]\n*[[Francis Bourke]]\n*[[Dan Minogue]]\n*[[Bill Morris (Australian rules footballer)|Bill Morris]]\n*[[Charlie Pannam (footballer, born 1874)|Charlie Pannam]]\n*[[Vic Thorp]]\n*[[Jack Titus]]\n*[[Dale Weightman]]\n*[[Roy Wright (footballer)|Roy Wright]]\n*[[Matthew Richardson (footballer)|Matthew Richardson]]\n*[[Maurice Rioli]]\n\nAs coaches of the game:\n*[[Tom Hafey]]\n*[[Frank 'Checker' Hughes]]\n\n===Richmond Hall of Fame===\nThe Richmond 'Hall of Fame' was created in 2002, with 24 inaugural inductees. Since then there have been a further ten batches of inductees added, most recently in 2019, for a total of 63 members. Below is a list of members, their contributions to the club, and the year they were inducted.<ref>{{cite web |title=Richmond Hall of Fame |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070317035606/http://www.richmondfc.com.au/TheClub/History/HallofFame/tabid/7638/Default.aspx |website=Internet Archive Wayback Machine |publisher=[[Australian Football League]] |accessdate=9 June 2019 |date=2007}}</ref><ref name=\"RFCHOF\">{{cite web |title=Welcome To Tigerland: Hall of Fame |url=https://www.richmondfc.com.au/club/history/hall-of-fame |website=RFC Official Site |publisher=[[Australian Football League]] |accessdate=9 June 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"TAHOF\">{{cite web |last1=Bartlett |first1=Rhett |last2=Ruddell |first2=Trevor |title=Richmond Hall of Fame |url=https://www.tigerlandarchive.org/tiki-index.php?page=Richmond+Hall+of+Fame |website=Tigerland Archive: Richmond Football Club history (1885 - Now) |accessdate=9 June 2019}}</ref> To date, eight Richmond \"''Immortals''\" have been named, the highest level of honour within the Hall of Fame. The first of these was [[Jack Dyer]], who was immediately made an 'immortal' upon his induction into the Hall of Fame in 2002, the year before his death.<ref name=\"dean-immortal\">{{cite web |last1=Greenberg |first1=Tony |title=Roger Dean honoured as Tiger 'Immortal' |url=https://www.richmondfc.com.au/news/2019-03-15/roger-dean-honoured-as-tiger-immortal |website=Richmond FC Official Site |publisher=[[Australian Football League]] |accessdate=4 June 2019 |date=15 March 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"titus-immortal\">{{cite web |last1=Greenberg |first1=Tony |title=Jack Titus elevated to Richmond 'Immortal' |url=https://www.richmondfc.com.au/news/2019-03-15/jack-titus-elevated-to-richmond-immortal-?camefrom=EMCL_2794945_132024951 |website=Richmond FC Official Site |publisher=[[Australian Football League]] |accessdate=29 May 2019 |date=15 March 2019}}</ref> The ''Immortals'' are highlighted in yellow in the table below.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 120px; text-align:left;\" | Name\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 80px; text-align:left;\" | Category\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | Career (at Richmond)\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 110px; text-align:center;\" | Year Inducted\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 110px; text-align:center;\" | Year 'Immortal'\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Baggot, Jack\"|[[Jack Baggott]]\n| Player\n| 1927\u201335\n| style=\"text-align:center; | 2019\n| data-sort-value=\"9999\"|\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Balme, Neil\"|[[Neil Balme]]\n| Player\n| 1970\u201379 (player), 2017\u2013current (administration)\n| style=\"text-align:center; | 2010\n| data-sort-value=\"9999\"|\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Barrot, Bill\"|[[Bill Barrot]]\n| Player\n| 1961\u201370\n| style=\"text-align:center; | 2007\n| data-sort-value=\"9999\"|\n|- style=\"background:#FEFC75;\"\n| data-sort-value=\"Bartlett, Kevin\"|[[Kevin Bartlett (Aussie Rules footballer)|Kevin Bartlett]]\n| Player\n| 1965\u201383 (player), 1988\u201391 (coach)\n| style=\"text-align:center; | 2002\n| style=\"text-align:center; |2004\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Bentley, Percy\"|[[Percy Bentley]]\n| Player\n| 1925\u201340 (player), 1934\u201340 (coach)\n| style=\"text-align:center; | 2002</small>\n| data-sort-value=\"9999\"|\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Bolger, Martin\"|[[Martin Bolger]]\n| Player\n| 1930\u201339 (player), 1940\u201375 (admin)\n| style=\"text-align:center; | 2005\n| data-sort-value=\"9999\"|\n|- style=\"background:#FEFC75;\"\n| data-sort-value=\"Bourke, Francis\"|[[Francis Bourke]]\n| Player\n| 1967\u201381 (player), 1982\u201383 (coach), 1992\u201394 (admin)\n| style=\"text-align:center; | 2002\n| style=\"text-align:center; | 2005\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Branton, Ron\"|[[Ron Branton]]\n| Player\n| 1953\u201362\n| style=\